<br>
Here in England the government will watch your back for you if you're in trouble. They will pay your rent and a small amount of money so that you can survive and they will pay for your healthcare and education. However, you have to have a good reason for not having a job. If you're just lazy then they stop your benefits.<br>
<br>
The system is nice; education and healthcare are free. Taxes aren't enormous. There are still rich people and poor people but very few people are struggling for survival. Having a socialist government does not destroy the economy - look at France, Germany, Japan, U.K., all have had they're booms and busts in recent years but that's as it always is under any system.<br>
<br>
The system has two problems.<br>
<br>
1) Some people still slip through the net. Not many, but some do.<br>
<br>
2) Benefit Fraud. Some people fraudulently claim benefits. But this is not a large proportion. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>The vast majority of people who claim benefits actually need benefits.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Couple of people are making out like anyone who needs benefits is a cheat and that simply isn't true.<br>
<br>
